e]], Finnish hurdler and politician\n*  1958   &ndash; [[Margaret Colin]], American actress\n*[[1959]] &ndash; [[Ole Bornedal]], Danish actor, director, and producer\n*[[1960]] &ndash; [[Doug Hutchison]], American actor\n*  1960   &ndash; [[Dean Lukin]], Australian weightlifter\n*  1960   &ndash; [[Masahiro Matsunaga]], Japanese race car driver\n*  1960   &ndash; [[Rob Murphy]], American baseball player\n*  1960   &ndash; [[Romas Ubartas]], Lithuanian discus thrower\n*[[1961]] &ndash; [[Steve Pate]], American golfer\n*  1961   &ndash; [[Tarsem Singh]], Indian-American director, producer, and screenwriter\n*[[1962]] &ndash; [[Black (singer)|Black]], English singer-songwriter (d. 2016)\n*[[1962]] &ndash; [[Genie Francis]], Canadian-American actress\n*  1962   &ndash; [[Bobcat Goldthwait]], American actor, director, and screenwriter\n*[[1963]] &ndash; [[Simon Armitage]], English poet, playwright and novelist\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Claude Legault]], Canadian actor and screenwriter\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Mary Nightingale]], English journalist\n*  1963   &ndash; [[Jamie Spence]], English golfer\n*[[1964]] &ndash; [[Caitl\u00edn R. Kiernan]], Irish-American paleontologist and author\n*  1964   &ndash; [[Lenny Kravitz]], American singer-songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, producer, and actor\n*  1964   &ndash; [[Argiris Pedoulakis]], Greek basketball player and coach\n*[[1965]] &ndash; [[Hazel Irvine]], Scottish sportscaster and journalist\n*[[1966]] &ndash; [[Helena Bonham Carter]], English actress \n*  1966   &ndash; [[Zola Budd]], South African runner\n*[[1967]] &ndash; [[Philip Treacy]], Irish milliner, hat designer\n*  1967   &ndash; [[Mika Yamamoto]], Japanese journalist (d. 2012)\n*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Fernando Le\u00f3n de Aranoa]], Spanish director, producer, and screenwriter\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Frederik, Crown Prince of Denmark]]\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Steve Sedgley]], English footballer and manager\n*[[1969]] &ndash; [[John Baird (Canadian politician)|John Baird]], Canadian politician, 10th [[Minister of Foreign Affairs (Canada)|Canadian Minister of Foreign Affairs]]\n*  1969   &ndash; [[Siri Lindley]], American triathlete and coach\n*  1969   &ndash; [[Dominic Mohan]], English journalist\n*[[1970]] &ndash; [[Nobuhiro Watsuki]], Japanese illustrator\n*[[1971]] &ndash; [[Zaher Andary]], Lebanese footballer\n*  1971   &ndash; [[Matt Stone]], American actor, animator, screenwriter, producer, and composer\n*[[1973]] &ndash; [[Naomi Harris]], Canadian-American photographer\n*[[1974]] &ndash; [[Lars Fr\u00f6lander]], Swedish swimmer\n*[[1975]] &ndash; [[Lauryn Hill]], American singer-songwriter, producer, and actress \n*[[1976]] &ndash; [[Paul Collingwood]], English cricketer and coach\n*  1976   &ndash; [[Stephen Curry (comedian)|Stephen Curry]], Australian comedian and actor\n*  1976   &ndash; [[Kenny Florian]], American mixed martial artist and sportscaster\n*  1976   &ndash; [[Justin Pierre]], American singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer \n*[[1977]] &ndash; [[Nikos Chatzivrettas]], Greek basketball player\n*  1977   &ndash; [[Raina Telgemeier]], American author and cartoonist\n*  1977   &ndash; [[Luca Toni]], Italian footballer\n*  1977   &ndash; [[Misaki Ito]], Japanese actress and model\n*[[1978]] &ndash; [[Phil Elvrum]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*  1978   &ndash; [[Fabio Firmani]], Italian footballer\n*  1978   &ndash; [[Dan Parks]], Australian-Scottish rugby player\n*[[1979]] &ndash; [[Amanda Bauer]], American astronomer and academic\n*  1979   &ndash; [[Natalya Nazarova]], Russian sprinter\n*  1979   &ndash; [[Elisabeth Harnois]], American actress\n*  1979   &ndash; [[Mehmet Okur]], Turkish basketball player\n*[[1980]] &ndash; [[Louis-Jean Cormier]], Canadian singer and songwriter\n*[[1981]] &ndash; [[Robert Copeland]], Australian footballer\n*  1981   &ndash; [[Anthony Ervin]], American swimmer<ref>{{cite web|title=Anthony Ervin|url=https://www.olympic.org/anthony-ervin|publisher=International Olympic C